    <thetext>Description of problem:

Since I launch the last update on 2017/04/04, iw3lock starts and after a (unknown) time the keyboard and mouse become unresponsive. It is still possible to ssh on the machine.

Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable):

i3status-2.11-1.fc25.x86_64
i3-4.13-1.fc25.x86_64
i3lock-2.8-1.fc25.x86_64

How reproducible:

This is systematic

Steps to Reproduce:
1. install i3, i3lock and xautolock
2. edit ~/.config/i3/config then add the lines:

bindsym $mod+Pause exec i3lock -c 000000
exec --no-startup-id xautolock -time 5 -locker &apos;i3lock -c 000000&apos;

3. lock screen manualy bit hitting $mod and &apos;Pause&apos; button
4. wait about 5 minutes (I think the same time as specified in xautolock&apos;

Actual results:
Keyboard / mouse become unresponsive so I cannot leave the lock screen

Expected results:
Be able to type my password and unlock the station


Additional info:</thetext>
